abstract: The bank’s $13 billion purchase of E-Trade is expected to inspire more mergers among asset managers.
snippet: The bank’s $13 billion purchase of E-Trade is expected to inspire more mergers among asset managers.
lead_paragraph: A Wells Fargo settlement with the S.E.C. over abusive sales practices could be announced as soon as today, our colleague Emily Flitter reports. (Want this in your inbox each day? Sign up here.)

abstract: Gabriel Zucman and Emmanuel Saez have crashed the Democratic primary with their idea — and angered some economists.
snippet: Gabriel Zucman and Emmanuel Saez have crashed the Democratic primary with their idea — and angered some economists.
lead_paragraph: BERKELEY, Calif. — One of the most liberal policy proposals animating the Democratic presidential primaries is the handiwork of two French economists who are not formally advising any campaign and have barely met the candidates running for the White House.

abstract: His performance in the first debate was abysmal. But it seems that Americans are eager to give billionaires a second chance.
snippet: His performance in the first debate was abysmal. But it seems that Americans are eager to give billionaires a second chance.
lead_paragraph: The conventional wisdom around Wednesday night’s presidential debate gelled almost immediately, adhering as if Gorilla Glue to the various deficiencies of Michael R. Bloomberg’s performance: He made a terrible case for himself; Elizabeth Warren was pulverizing him. His poll numbers, high before the debate and Bernie Sanders’s primary win in Nevada, have since declined.

abstract: Does the world belong to them or to us?
snippet: Does the world belong to them or to us?
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders wants to get rid of them. Amy Klobuchar is fine with them, but wants them to pay somewhat higher taxes. Joe Biden promises them that under him, “nothing would fundamentally change.” Tom Steyer is one of them and wouldn’t be in the race if he wasn’t but seems slightly embarrassed about it. Elizabeth Warren wants to break up the companies that made many of them in the first place. Michael Bloomberg is trying to become president largely on the basis of being one. It would take Pete Buttigieg thousands of years to become one at his past rate of adult wealth creation, and yet he seems to be their top choice.

abstract: Malaysian telecoms firm Axiata Group is talking to eleven potential partners, including banks, to jointly bid for a digital banking license, its deputy chief executive, Mohd Izzaddin Idris, said on Friday.
snippet: Malaysian telecoms firm Axiata Group is talking to eleven potential partners, including banks, to jointly bid for a digital banking license, its deputy chief executive, Mohd Izzaddin Idris, said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR — Malaysian telecoms firm Axiata Group is talking to eleven potential partners, including banks, to jointly bid for a digital banking license, its deputy chief executive, Mohd Izzaddin Idris, said on Friday.
headline_main: Malaysia's Axiata in Talks With 11 to Partner Up for Bid on Digital Bank License
headline_print_headline: Malaysia's Axiata in Talks With 11 to Partner Up for Bid on Digital Bank License

abstract: Italy's biggest bank UniCredit may make an announcement as early as Friday night on the future of boss Jean Pierre Mustier, two sources familiar with the matter said, after reports he is vying for the top job at rival HSBC.
snippet: Italy's biggest bank UniCredit may make an announcement as early as Friday night on the future of boss Jean Pierre Mustier, two sources familiar with the matter said, after reports he is vying for the top job at rival HSBC.
lead_paragraph: MILAN — Italy's biggest bank UniCredit may make an announcement as early as Friday night on the future of boss Jean Pierre Mustier, two sources familiar with the matter said, after reports he is vying for the top job at rival HSBC.
headline_main: UniCredit May Make Announcement Soon on CEO Mustier's Future: Sources
